CatDescriptText: Elizabeth G. Henderson, state field representative of the Fair Employment Practices Commission, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 28, 1959, pg. A1, with question: "Do you think race relations are improved, are worse, or about the same today as compared to pre-World War II years?"  Answer reads: "They are definitely improved, although there is much to be done."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Elizabeth G. Henderson wearing dark double breasted coat, standing in front of Triangle Camera store window with sign advertising film projector for $39.50
